description._content: Description: Hanukkah lamp/Shabbat candleholder. Eight-branched candelabrum consisting of a base, shaft, branches and candle sockets with eagle finial. Rectangular stepped base raised on scrollwork with feet culminating in pedestal decorated with garlands, surmounted by stepped base with urn shaped shaft terminating in candle socket. Four double branches in foliate scroll form. Cup-shaped candle sockets on convex bases. Object origin: probably Vienna, Austria Date: approximately 1886-1922 Medium: silver Repository: Yeshiva University Museum Call Number: 1993.160 Persistent URL: access.cjh.org/411051 Rights Information: No known copyright restrictions; may be subject to third party rights.
